{
  "doc_id": "16037",
  "text": "Taverna [CITATION_1] is an open source workflow system particularly focused on bioinformatics applications and services, and it is based on the XScufl (XML Simple Conceptual Unified Flow) language. Kepler [CITATION_2] is a scientific workflow system that builds on the Ptolemy-II system (http://ptolemy.eecs.berkeley.edu/ptolemyII/), which is a visual modeling tool written in Java. Triana [CITATION_3] is a GUI-based workflow system for coordinating and executing a collection of services. All these systems have some visual interfaces (also referred to as workbenches) that allow the graphical composition of workflows.",
